<font color="#FF0000">VISITING THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec  8 18:04:30 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I have only visted the Wall through the media.  The recent<br>
documentary about the design, implemenation, and reaction <br>
to the Vietnam Memorial challenged me to link about <br>
creativity and interpretation of history.  The winning design<br>
was a triumphant success but I can't help but think that<br>
another kind of memorial should be considered as well.  I <br>
think something needs to be said about the utter futility of <br>
this War in particular.  A monument that is not a &quot;memorial&quot; <br>
to the lives lost, but rather a &quot;warning&quot; about a period in <br>
history that should never repeated.
<p><code>--   (John Wells) </code><p>


